# dwf — ignore rules
#
# Why this file exists (2026-07-11): the repo had an EMPTY .gitignore and ~23,400 untracked files
# (generated sprite renders, caches, logs) sitting alongside real source. That made `git add -A`
# genuinely dangerous — AGENTS.md hard rule 6 bans it — which in turn made every commit a manual
# minefield, which meant nobody committed, which meant a full day of work could sit unsaved.
# Ignoring the generated noise makes committing a boring, safe habit again.
#
# NOTE: .gitignore never UN-tracks anything. Files already committed under these paths (e.g. the
# ~1,634 tracked files under tools/spriterange/results/) stay tracked and still show when modified.
# These rules only stop NEW generated files from cluttering `git status`.

# --- generated sprite/render output (the ~23k problem) ---
tools/spriterange/results/
tools/spikes/render-buffer/

# --- python caches ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# --- agent/codex scratch ---
.tmp-codex-artifacts/

# --- flight-recorder corpus (ground-truth pipeline Pillar 2; session data, never source) ---
recordings/
dfcapture-recordings/

# --- generated ground-truth indexes and reports (source records live under docs/reference/) ---
/build/ground-truth/
/build/atlas/

# --- runtime logs ---
*.log

# --- OS / editor noise ---
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
# User-supplied comparison font. License is unverified; keep it local and never publish it.
web/fonts/dwarf-fortress-van-user.ttf

# --- W11 sprite provenance: DF-derived composites are BAKED, never committed ---
# The client sprites derive from the paid DF graphics. Hosts bake them at install
# time (host/bake_sprites.mjs + host/sprite_recipe.json); devs may regenerate them
# locally (tools/ws2/bake_dwarf.py, build_item_map.py, build_creature_map.py) for a
# deploy, but they must never be tracked again. Enforced by
# tools/harness/sprite_provenance_gate_test.mjs (fails on any tracked raster here).
web/dwarf.png
web/dwarf_dark.png
web/dwarf_female.png
web/animal_people_flat.png
web/item_chair_composite.png
web/item_hatch_composite.png
web/item_table_composite.png
web/favicon.png
tools/ws2/sprites/*.png
# agent worktrees (created inside the repo by wave agents)
wt/

# WER crash dumps (multi-GB full-process memory images -- never commit).
# A 2.5GB dump was once swept in by an `add -A` and GitHub rejected the push.
crashdumps/

# Generated review decks belong below tools/ or evidence/, never at repository root.
/*.html

# working handoff notes never belong at the repo root
HANDOFF-*.md

# W16 release packages are generated artifacts attached to GitHub Releases, never source.
/DwarfWithFriends-*.zip
/dist/
tools/demo/takes/

# Downloaded/vendor executables and generated release receipts are local artifacts.
/host/cloudflared.exe
/launch-manifest.json
/docs/stabilization/build-receipt-current.json

# headless-Chrome scratch dirs from the screen-truth rig
.screen-truth-chrome-*/
/release/
